conbody.p:
The array_insert function inserts a value into a specific position in an
        array and returns the new array.
        array array_insert( array-name, position, value)go_cbq> SELECT array_insert(schedule, 2, "jsmith")[2]  
         FROM `travel-sample` 
         WHERE type = "route"  
         LIMIT 1;
         {
         "requestID": "c0e073ed-5eca-451d-bcc2-57e2e01ab93d",
         "signature": {
         "$1": "json"
         },
         "results" : [
         {
         "$1": "jsmith"
         }
         ],
         "status": "success",
         "metrics": {
         "elapsedTime": "4.883422ms",
         "executionTime": "4.849777ms",
         "resultCount": 1,
         "resultSize": 38
         }
         }
